I am friends with Sticker Bob from Paddling, he reached out to me to see if I was interested in participating. I am. my instagram is @Saysayer and @TheTrashTramp As an outrigger canoe paddler in the ocean I am faced with trash daily. I imagine I used to paddle by trash without noticing but the shades have been lifted and for the past few years it seems I might seek out trash. I have been on a zero waste journey and although the goal might be unattainable I believe that I am becoming a better steward for the earth because of it. Our waste problem is more than we can handle as trash pickers alone. We need a greater awareness and we need to, as Marcus Eriksen Co-founder of @5gyres says \turn off the tap\" we need to stop this problem at the source and that is by holding producers responsible and by minimizing our waste creation as well as doing our job of cleaning up. If you can reduce your single use
column19: support businesses that are supporting you and the environment
column21: and be kind to each other. Each of us can make small changes that will add up. I started a small business to help spread awareness and help with the Trash crisis. @thetrashtramp is a device that I created to put on my canoe to hold the trash I collect while I continue to train. #TrainingOutTheTrash. I am currently selling shirts with the TrashTramp Logo made from recycled materials. I want to be the best human I can while I'm here. I am currently training for an 80 miles race in Florida from Bimini The Bahamas to Florida. It is a fundraiser for Cystic Fibrosis @crossingforcf. Follow my journey on Instagram @saysayer. I am inspired by all you outstanding humans cleaning up out there. It's a big tough and dirty job but we all have to do it. Let's Save the planet! Do it for the Birds!\"""}
